OL,3,CPolice officers under gross misconduct
OL,4,Cinvestigation in wrongful conviction
OL,5,Ccase
OL,7,F"One of the officers has also been
OL,8,Fnotified that they are under criminal
OL,9,Finvestigation for potential misconduct
OL,10,Fin public office and perverting the
OL,11,Fcourse of justice in relation to their
OL,12,Factions during the police
OL,13,Finvestigation and subsequent trial.
OL,15,F"Our investigation team continues to
OL,16,Fwork hard to conclude our
OL,17,Finvestigation as soon as reasonably
OL,18,Fpossible, while ensuring our inquiries
OL,19,Fdo not prejudice separate criminal
OL,20,Fmatters linked to the crime Mr
OL,21,FMalkinson was wrongly convicted of.
OL,26,@oD@AOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/11
